          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Echo Chamber Studios, mid-tier recording studio in Nashville. Website: basic single page with equipment list only ("Neve console, Pro Tools, various mics"). No audio samples, no client work examples, pricing hidden ("contact for quote"), booking through email only. Monthly bookings: 8 sessions @ $1,500 average = $12,000 revenue. Problem: "Artists ask same questions repeatedly: 'What does the drum room sound like?' 'Can I hear examples of vocal recordings?' 'How much for full production?' I spend 3 hours daily answering emails, losing bookings to studios with samples visible. Artists book with studios they can HEAR, not read about."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-purple-50 border-[3px] border-purple-400 p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-purple-900 text-lg mb-4">THE TRANSFORMATION</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">December 1, 2024 (5-day Squarespace build): Professional studio portfolio with before/after audio samples prominently (raw vocal vs. mixed/mastered comparison, drum room samples, guitar amp A/B comparisons), equipment gallery detailed (Neve 1073 preamps specified, U47 microphone listed, Apollo interface shown), package pricing transparent ("Full Production: $2,500/day • Mixing Only: $800/song • Mastering: $150/song"), client testimonials with album clips (artist quotes, Spotify links to completed tracks), online booking system (Calendly integration, deposit required), mobile-optimized audio player (79% of musicians browse on phones). Budget: $1,400 (Squarespace annual $276 + audio sample editing $400 + 20 hours studio time @ $30/hr).</p>
