          <div>
            <p class="font-black text-red-700 mb-3">✗ CONS</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
              <li>• Performance issues (PageSpeed 62-71, slow audio loading)</li>
              <li>• Template lock-in (switching = rebuild content)</li>
              <li>• Monthly pricing (no annual discount)</li>
              <li>• Booking learning curve (setup takes time)</li>
              <li>• Equipment gallery basic (no filtering/search)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-purple-300 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">PERFORMANCE: High-Volume Booking Studio Case Study</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">SoundHouse Recording, high-volume studio (rehearsal rooms + recording), needed booking system for hourly rentals (multiple rooms, overlapping sessions). Built Wix site (January 2025): Wix Bookings integration (room calendars visible, real-time availability), package pricing ($50/hour rehearsal, $100/hour recording, $400/day lockout), mobile app (studio owner manages bookings from phone), equipment list per room (Room A has Neve, Room B has API). Results: Bookings increased from 124 hours/month to 187 hours/month (51% increase). Revenue: $6,200/month → $12,400/month (100% increase). No-shows decreased 67% (deposit required at booking, automated reminders). Administrative time: 4 hours daily → 1 hour (booking automation handles scheduling, payments). Build cost: $900 (Wix $204/year + Wix Bookings add-on $300/year + 10 hours setup). ROI: 100% revenue increase, 1-month payback 13x. Key insight: Wix Bookings built-in = powerful for high-volume studios (multiple rooms, hourly bookings, overlapping sessions). Real-time availability visible = artists book available slots without emailing back-and-forth. Deposit required = no-shows reduced 67% (artists invested, show up). Mobile app = owner manages bookings anywhere (rehearsal studio business = always on-the-go). But performance issues = audio samples load slowly (PageSpeed 62-71 vs. Squarespace 84). Artists skip waiting, assume low quality. Wix wins for: rehearsal studios needing hourly booking, multi-room facilities requiring availability calendars, budget-conscious studios ($17/month cheaper than Squarespace). But avoid if: portfolio quality critical (audio samples must load fast), premium positioning required (Wix templates look generic), established studio with referral-only bookings (no need for public booking system).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Webflow -->
      <div class="mb-12 border-[3px] border-violet-300 p-8 bg-violet-50">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-6">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">Webflow AI</h3>
